subsection.def:
action
                    (訴訟) includes any proceeding in a court of
                law;

rent
                    (租金) includes a rentcharge and a rent
                service;

ship
                    (船舶) includes every description of vessel
                used in navigation not propelled solely by oars;

the court (法院), in
                relation to an action, means the court in which the action has been, or is intended
                to be, brought;

paragraph.content:
in the case of an action for an account, be construed as references to the
                    date on which the matter arose in respect of which an account is
                    claimed;

this section shall not affect any case where the right of action
                            first accrued to some person (not under a disability) through whom the
                            person under a disability claims;

that that injury was attributable in whole or in part to the act or
                    omission which is alleged to constitute negligence, nuisance or breach of duty;
                    and
